<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-30T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-30T20:00:00-05:00" n="420" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7460: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Peck</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-01T09:00:00+08:00">December 1, 1935—9
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 1—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>121. Ho Ying-chin, appointed Executive Yuan representative in Peiping,
                            accompanied by Chen Yi, Provincial Chairman [of] Fukien, and Hsiung
                            Shih-hui, Provincial Chairman [of] Kiangsi, left Nanking by special
                            train November 30, 10 p.m. for Peiping to deal with Sino-Japanese
                            relations.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Peck</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>